The **Admin Management** page allows organizations to assign employees to different administrative roles within their VoxDash account.

![][image1]

## **To add a new administrator:**

1. Click the **"Add User"** button located at the top right corner of the page.

2. In the pop-up form, fill in the required user details (e.g., name, email address).

3. Select an **Access Level** from the available roles:
* **Administrator**: Full control over data, user management (including other admins and data users), and all system settings.
* **Editor**: Can edit project-related data but cannot manage users or system-wide settings.
* **Analyst**: Has view-only access to reports and dashboards. Cannot edit or manage any data or users.

4. Click **"Send Invitation"**.

An invitation email will be sent to the specified email address, inviting the user to join **VoxDash** under your organization with the selected role.

Once the user accepts the invitation, they will be able to access the platform with the assigned permissions.

### **Note:** Only users with Administrator access can add or modify other users.
